1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:02,010
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,010 --> 00:00:03,710
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:04,210 --> 00:00:05,510
- You know what this is?
- Let go.

4
00:00:05,580 --> 00:00:08,450
- Let go.
- You wanted proof? Here it is!

5
00:00:08,510 --> 00:00:09,510
Hurry up and take a picture.

6
00:00:09,580 --> 00:00:11,550
My gosh, this is ridiculous.
Let go of my phone.

7
00:00:11,620 --> 00:00:12,820
- You think this scares me?
- My!

8
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:13,890
Let go, you jerk.

9
00:00:13,950 --> 00:00:15,390
I can't believe you pulled this.
Seriously.

10
00:00:15,450 --> 00:00:17,460
I'm an expert. I can tell everything
just by holding your wrist.

11
00:00:17,460 --> 00:00:20,830
- Let go of it!
- What's this commotion so late?

12
00:00:20,890 --> 00:00:25,830
Officer, these people are trying
to forcibly take our property.

13
00:00:25,960 --> 00:00:30,500
Your wife posted my picture online
and started a rumor about an affair!

14
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:34,610
- Listen, that's...
- Wait. Let go, then we'll talk.

15
00:00:35,010 --> 00:00:37,980
The definitive proof is
on this phone.

16
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:40,480
We're pressing defamation charges.
Got it?

17
00:00:40,550 --> 00:00:43,750
My gosh! Please. Go right ahead.
We'll countersue for false charges.

18
00:00:43,750 --> 00:00:45,080
- Do it. Go for it!
- Goodness.

19
00:00:45,180 --> 00:00:47,190
- Can you shut your trap?
- False accusations?

20
00:00:47,250 --> 00:00:48,550
- You let go first!
- Unbelievable.

21
00:00:48,620 --> 00:00:49,890
- You take your hands off.
- Hey!

22
00:00:49,890 --> 00:00:51,190
Seriously, why you...

23
00:00:53,990 --> 00:00:57,230
All right, I'm taking all of you in.
Let's go to the police substation.

24
00:00:57,300 --> 00:01:00,930
- The substation? Why us?
- But they're the ones at fault.

25
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:03,100
Why are you taking us in, too?

26
00:01:03,170 --> 00:01:07,370
Possible assault, attempted robbery.
If you refuse to cooperate,

27
00:01:08,110 --> 00:01:09,940
I'll have no choice
but to place you under arrest.

28
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:21,220
I'm telling you,
the proof is on that phone!

29
00:01:21,990 --> 00:01:25,620
- Are you sure?
- That's why they fought so hard.

30
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:27,290
Ma'am, let me see the phone.

31
00:01:28,390 --> 00:01:30,560
- Excuse me?
- I just need to check it.

32
00:01:31,130 --> 00:01:33,060
If you continue to refuse,
you'll only make things worse.

33
00:01:42,710 --> 00:01:44,710
(Police, Information)

34
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:48,410
(Respect for Human Rights,
Fairness, and Kindness)

35
00:01:52,220 --> 00:01:54,090
- What?
- What's wrong?

36
00:01:54,090 --> 00:01:55,390
The photo...

37
00:01:56,150 --> 00:01:58,220
- It's not here.
- What?

38
00:01:58,990 --> 00:02:00,330
That's impossible.

39
00:02:00,690 --> 00:02:03,090
- Keep scrolling.
- Yes.

40
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,000
It's really not here.

41
00:02:06,130 --> 00:02:10,130
All I see are pictures of food,
flowers, and landscapes.

42
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:11,800
See? He said it's not there.

43
00:02:12,470 --> 00:02:14,070
He says it's not there.

44
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,010
Are you sure you aren't mistaken?

45
00:02:16,980 --> 00:02:19,140
I am absolutely speechless.

46
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:21,480
But you were in Seoul today!

47
00:02:22,380 --> 00:02:23,380
Weren't you?

48
00:02:23,550 --> 00:02:26,250
I'm way too busy
to have gone to Seoul.

49
00:02:26,550 --> 00:02:29,120
What?
Do you want me to prove my alibi?

50
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,460
Honey, she said she didn't go.

51
00:02:33,290 --> 00:02:38,160
- I'm telling you. I saw her.
- You're wrong. You have bad eyes.

52
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:42,300
Actually, that happens to me
from time to time as well.

53
00:02:43,540 --> 00:02:45,600
I know you want to blame someone,
but honestly.

54
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:48,140
You can't just gang up
on people like this.

55
00:02:48,870 --> 00:02:50,940
Part of me wants to demand
an apology,

56
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:53,510
but let's just leave it at that.

57
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:57,950
Officer, are we free to go now?

58
00:02:58,250 --> 00:02:59,550
Yes, you may go.

59
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,590
Have a good night.

60
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:02,890
Unbelievable.

61
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:05,320
Let's go.

62
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,630
His family and my family...

63
00:03:15,970 --> 00:03:18,170
are sworn enemies.

64
00:03:18,770 --> 00:03:21,040
It's a blood feud
passed down through generations.

65
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:26,340
I see.

66
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:30,150
Anyway,
what's your real Korean name?

67
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:33,520
My name.

68
00:03:34,790 --> 00:03:35,990
My name is...

69
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:38,260
Yang...

70
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:42,790
Yang, I know that much.
What comes after?

71
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:49,600
Hold on a second.

72
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:51,340
Honestly.

73
00:03:52,070 --> 00:03:53,100
Woo Jae? What is it?

74
00:03:55,110 --> 00:03:56,110
What?

75
00:03:57,310 --> 00:03:58,410
What about Mom?

76
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:02,510
Okay, I'm on my way now.

77
00:04:03,650 --> 00:04:07,320
Sir. Something urgent has come up,
and I have to go.

78
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:08,590
- I'm really sorry.
- What?

79
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:10,250
Darn it.

80
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,460
- You're back.
- Yes.

81
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:19,860
Se Ri.

82
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:22,930
Se Ri, you're the one
who posted that photo, right?

83
00:04:23,370 --> 00:04:25,670
My goodness, Dong Suk.
What an awful thing to say.

84
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:29,210
Come on. I know it was you.
Why hide it from me?

85
00:04:29,540 --> 00:04:32,880
Don't you dare repeat that.
Don't breathe a word of this, okay?

86
00:04:34,610 --> 00:04:35,610
My goodness.

87
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:39,980
What are you talking about, Auntie?
What picture did my stepmom post?

88
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,120
- I don't know.
- Auntie!

89
00:04:42,190 --> 00:04:44,460
Didn't you hear him?
I'm not supposed to breathe a word.

90
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,460
Good grief.

91
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,790
What's so interesting
on that darn phone of yours?

92
00:04:50,060 --> 00:04:52,660
Go to your room.
Can't you read the room?

93
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,830
- Auntie.
- I told you, I don't know.

94
00:04:55,230 --> 00:04:56,230
Seriously...

95
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:02,410
That was a close call.

96
00:05:02,770 --> 00:05:06,340
I know. If I hadn't deleted it,
we would've been in real trouble.

97
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:08,950
I never imagined
she would have seen me.

98
00:05:09,010 --> 00:05:11,820
Those people can never find out
you were behind this.

99
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:14,550
Don't worry. She'll just think
she was seeing things.

100
00:05:15,620 --> 00:05:16,620
By the way...

101
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:19,790
Was the studio apartment you were
getting for Hyun Bin near there?

102
00:05:19,990 --> 00:05:23,160
Yes, it looks like
her clinic is in that area, too.

103
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:32,000
When on earth are you going to
tell her who you are?

104
00:05:33,170 --> 00:05:36,510
I don't know.
I'm not sure I even need to.

105
00:05:36,910 --> 00:05:39,340
I'm leaving in one year anyway.

106
00:05:39,610 --> 00:05:41,710
Didn't you plan on seeing her at all
when you came back to Korea?

107
00:05:42,350 --> 00:05:45,980
I thought of seeing her from afar.
Like during my military service.

108
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:49,490
But you met her like this,

109
00:05:49,490 --> 00:05:51,490
and you even asked
to move her to your office.

110
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:56,430
I told you.
I didn't have some ulterior motive.

111
00:05:56,930 --> 00:05:58,130
So, what's it like seeing her again?

112
00:05:58,930 --> 00:05:59,960
Do you still like her?

113
00:06:01,130 --> 00:06:02,130
It's just...

114
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:04,500
It's nice to see her, I guess.

115
00:06:05,340 --> 00:06:07,740
I had a childhood crush on her
because she seemed so cool,

116
00:06:08,370 --> 00:06:10,610
but I doubt that'll happen now.

117
00:06:11,110 --> 00:06:13,480
We're just coworkers.

118
00:06:15,410 --> 00:06:17,010
You never know.

119
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,620
You might fall for her again.

120
00:06:28,990 --> 00:06:30,260
People are going wild, aren't they?

121
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:31,660
Of course, they are.

122
00:06:31,660 --> 00:06:33,730
My husband had an affair
and ran off.

123
00:06:33,970 --> 00:06:35,870
They all say
I'm so unlucky because...

124
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:37,500
my daughter-in-law is cheating, too.

125
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:40,970
My gosh. People will say anything,
won't they?

126
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:44,240
I wouldn't feel so wronged
if it were true.

127
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,480
I know.

128
00:06:45,910 --> 00:06:49,450
Your husband is always in trouble
and doesn't even make good money.

129
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:53,990
You're so young and pretty.
I wouldn't blame you for cheating.

130
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:56,820
Mother! Someone will hear you.

131
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,120
Ju Ah.

132
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:02,190
Mom, are you really cheating?

133
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:05,430
- Ju Ah.
- Are you cheating? Answer me!

134
00:07:05,430 --> 00:07:06,460
Hey.

135
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:09,800
Have you been drinking again?
Will you be like this every day?

136
00:07:09,870 --> 00:07:12,400
Don't deflect, and tell me straight.
Are you having an affair?

137
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,040
Hey, seriously...
Will you keep your voice down?

138
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:17,070
Hey, Ju Ah, go on inside.
It's late. Hurry up.

139
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,650
Where do you think you're going?
I asked if you're having an affair!

140
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:22,880
Oh, dear.

141
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:27,320
No! I told you. I'm not!

142
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:29,190
Then what's with that photo?

143
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:31,560
Do you know what people are saying
in the comments?

144
00:07:31,820 --> 00:07:33,990
They say you're
"Adultery Evangelist,"

145
00:07:33,990 --> 00:07:35,530
not "Love Evangelist."

146
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:39,330
- Why, you...
- My goodness. Hey!

147
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:40,730
Hey.

148
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,100
Why are you misunderstanding
your mom like this?

149
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:46,340
What misunderstanding, Grandma?
Where there's smoke, there's fire.

150
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:49,070
You've always been like this.

151
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:52,310
You said you only married Dad
because of me, right?

152
00:07:52,810 --> 00:07:56,580
You ignored Dad, mistreated him,
and yelled at him over small things.

153
00:07:56,980 --> 00:07:59,920
Now, you're rich and famous,
so you decide to cheat?

154
00:08:00,350 --> 00:08:03,220
- Is this why you moved out?
- Hey.

155
00:08:03,490 --> 00:08:05,920
No, wait. Mom...

156
00:08:06,490 --> 00:08:07,990
Are you even really living alone?

157
00:08:08,290 --> 00:08:09,290
Ju Ah!

158
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:13,870
The whole world can misunderstand me
and curse my name,

159
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:16,800
but shouldn't you be the one person
who trusts me?

160
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:19,370
You never believed in me.
Why should I?

161
00:08:19,370 --> 00:08:22,370
Hey, get inside. Now.
Go on, get in there.

162
00:08:23,770 --> 00:08:24,910
Have you been drinking?

163
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:26,580
Have you?

164
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:38,520
Really.

165
00:08:40,590 --> 00:08:43,360
Who on earth talks to their mother
like that?

166
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,660
What mother says such awful things
to her own child?

167
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:51,100
She always said she only married Dad
because of me.

168
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:56,770
Your mom was younger than you are
when she said that.

169
00:08:57,380 --> 00:09:00,950
Why take to heart what she said
when she was young and naive?

170
00:09:01,010 --> 00:09:02,810
Because it cut me to the core.

171
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:05,720
Honestly, I just can't...

172
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,890
Are you okay, Grandma?

173
00:09:10,890 --> 00:09:13,120
While your mother was raising you,

174
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:15,990
I was afraid she'd regret
quitting her studies,

175
00:09:16,930 --> 00:09:21,230
so I insisted on raising you myself.
I barely let her touch you.

176
00:09:22,530 --> 00:09:25,740
And I wonder if that's why
you never bonded with your mother.

177
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:29,710
It breaks my heart
every time you act like this.

178
00:09:30,780 --> 00:09:32,280
I'm sorry, Grandma.

179
00:09:33,180 --> 00:09:34,880
I know, I was wrong.

180
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:39,750
Don't hurt your mom's feelings.
You'll regret it later.

181
00:09:41,350 --> 00:09:42,720
I won't.

182
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:48,060
- Get some rest.
- Okay.

183
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:53,360
Gosh, seriously...

184
00:09:56,430 --> 00:09:58,840
(Taehan)

185
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:10,510
Mom. I was too harsh yesterday.

186
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,850
Sorry.

187
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,220
(Mom, I was too harsh yesterday.
Sorry.)

188
00:10:15,450 --> 00:10:16,450
No...

189
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:17,620
(Mom, I was too harsh yesterday.
Sorry.)

190
00:10:18,590 --> 00:10:21,530
What was so harsh about it?
It's not like I was wrong.

191
00:10:27,130 --> 00:10:29,370
Sorry, I'm late.
I had an executive meeting.

192
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:31,700
Why? Because of
the product review and budget?

193
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,140
Did they shoot everything down?

194
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,370
Oh, well...

195
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:37,710
The design team meeting
is about to start,

196
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,510
so let's talk about it then.

197
00:10:42,050 --> 00:10:43,080
That's okay.

198
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,920
I hope everyone got home okay
last night.

199
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,050
Yes. It's a shame
we couldn't stay out longer.

200
00:10:49,820 --> 00:10:52,620
How about we party all night
at the workshop next week?

201
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,660
- Yes, I love that!
- Sounds great!

202
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:57,830
And the proposal from yesterday...

203
00:10:57,830 --> 00:10:59,900
It was approved
at the executive meeting today.

204
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,330
- Nice.
- That's awesome!

205
00:11:01,970 --> 00:11:02,970
The product review proposal...

206
00:11:03,370 --> 00:11:07,100
- and the budget increase? Both?
- Yes. But...

207
00:11:08,270 --> 00:11:09,610
there's one condition.

208
00:11:10,740 --> 00:11:12,540
What's the condition?

209
00:11:13,710 --> 00:11:16,880
At the upcoming
Korea Fashion Design Competition,

210
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:18,620
we need to have a winning design.

211
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:21,690
What? But isn't its deadline
just around the corner?

212
00:11:21,820 --> 00:11:24,520
Gosh, we also have to prepare
for the Hot Summer collection.

213
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:26,790
So won't we be a little pressed
for time?

214
00:11:27,830 --> 00:11:31,830
Use designs from your portfolios,
past competitions, or reviews.

215
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:33,630
I want you to use designs
that were previously rejected.

216
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:38,200
Submit a design you're confident in
by tomorrow. The final selection...

217
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:42,910
will be made by an internal vote
from employees in other departments.

218
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:45,710
- Okay.
- Got it.

219
00:11:46,310 --> 00:11:47,340
Right.

220
00:11:47,610 --> 00:11:51,050
The winning design will be
publicly credited to the designer.

221
00:11:52,020 --> 00:11:53,520
- It'll be credited?
- Yes.

222
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:55,690
The designer's name
will be on the label.

223
00:11:56,050 --> 00:11:57,350
- Really?
- For real?

224
00:11:58,220 --> 00:12:00,420
My gosh. What should I submit?

225
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,130
What about your Metro Classic one?

226
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:04,630
Where did I put it?
Please tell me I didn't delete it.

227
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:26,980
Is this one better?

228
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:37,760
Wow, everyone's in
full-on competition mode.

229
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:41,630
I bet no one's going home
or getting any sleep tonight.

230
00:12:42,170 --> 00:12:45,840
Is it really that big of a deal
to have your name on your design?

231
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:50,840
Sir, you really have no idea
what you've started, do you?

232
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:54,040
Not really.
I thought it was only natural.

233
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:58,420
I always wondered why clothes
only have the brand name on them.

234
00:12:58,620 --> 00:12:59,780
That's exactly it.

235
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:03,150
You've acknowledged
the designer's worth.

236
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:05,360
Is that how it comes across?

237
00:13:06,460 --> 00:13:09,530
Why else are designers so desperate
to have their own labels?

238
00:13:10,690 --> 00:13:12,660
It's just a shame
you don't realize...

239
00:13:12,730 --> 00:13:14,970
how truly exciting this is.

240
00:13:16,370 --> 00:13:18,500
I'll look forward to seeing
your design, Ms. Gong.

241
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:20,500
Yes. I'm looking forward to it, too.

242
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:25,780
I'll design one with my name on it
and have my grandma wear it.

243
00:13:25,940 --> 00:13:29,950
I'll finally take my mom,
who looks down on me, down a peg.

244
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:31,120
Yes!

245
00:13:31,850 --> 00:13:33,150
Gosh, which one is better?

246
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:47,900
So, what's the update?

247
00:13:48,130 --> 00:13:50,730
For now, I've blocked
the reporters' fact-checking calls.

248
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,270
So we're not going to issue
a counter-statement?

249
00:13:53,870 --> 00:13:55,710
No, I mean,
no articles have been published yet.

250
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,370
And it's not even true.

251
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:59,710
If we put out a statement now,
it'll just exaggerate the situation.

252
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:03,150
Hey. What about the contract
that's on hold?

253
00:14:03,310 --> 00:14:07,690
Oh, one of our writers had an idea
for you and Jeong Han.

254
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:09,950
We could film some content
of you two getting along...

255
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:12,590
and use that to open the show.

256
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:18,630
We are getting along fine.
We just see each other on weekends.

257
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:20,360
Yes, I know. I get it, but...

258
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:23,230
we have to think about the viewers.
That's why we should do it.

259
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:26,840
They believe whatever they see.
Just look at what's happening now.

260
00:14:29,740 --> 00:14:31,680
I hadn't considered that.

261
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:35,410
- Hello. Vote for number two!
- Hello.

262
00:14:35,510 --> 00:14:37,950
- Hello. We're with Gong Jeong Han.
- Hello.

263
00:14:38,020 --> 00:14:39,620
- We're counting on your vote!
- For Candidate Number Two!

264
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:41,320
- Hey, Dae Han.
- Yes, sir?

265
00:14:41,390 --> 00:14:45,720
Gong's wife, the TV doctor.
I heard she had an affair?

266
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:48,560
What? Who told you that?
Who? That's not true!

267
00:14:48,630 --> 00:14:50,360
I'm very disappointed.

268
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:53,800
I'm not voting for Dr. Gong.

269
00:14:53,860 --> 00:14:56,230
No, I'm telling you it's not true!
Sir, please.

270
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:58,640
Seriously,
that's not what happened, everyone.

271
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:03,270
But I heard people say Dr. Gong
is going to drop out of the race.

272
00:15:03,270 --> 00:15:04,280
That's not true!

273
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:05,780
- Who's behind these crazy rumors?
- What?

274
00:15:06,340 --> 00:15:08,010
Uncle, look.

275
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:16,520
There she is.
The source of these vicious rumors.

276
00:15:18,690 --> 00:15:19,990
I'm telling you. It's true.

277
00:15:20,290 --> 00:15:23,430
Everyone in Onjeong Market knows
Dr. Gong's wife is cheating...

278
00:15:23,490 --> 00:15:25,960
You evil-tongued gossip!
I will be sure...

279
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,830
- to teach you a lesson today.
- Hey!

280
00:15:27,830 --> 00:15:28,870
Hey.

281
00:15:28,930 --> 00:15:30,200
What are you doing here?

282
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,370
- I will shut you up for good today!
- Let go!

283
00:15:34,610 --> 00:15:36,910
Hey! You're disgusting!

284
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,810
What are you talking about?
I didn't spread any rumors.

285
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:42,150
It was you!
You're the one spreading lies!

286
00:15:42,210 --> 00:15:44,780
What lies?
I'm just saying what's in the photo.

287
00:15:44,850 --> 00:15:46,220
- It's real?
- It's real.

288
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:48,750
Who would take such a photo
and post it online?

289
00:15:48,990 --> 00:15:51,260
Yes, I wonder
who could have done such a thing.

290
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:54,490
- My stepmom did it.
- What?

291
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:57,060
So go ahead and sue her!
I'll be the witness.

292
00:15:57,130 --> 00:15:58,760
Hey. Stop talking nonsense.

293
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:00,500
It'll be chaos
if the adults believe you.

294
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:03,330
I'm telling you, it's true!
For the doctor falsely accused,

295
00:16:03,330 --> 00:16:04,970
I'm making a noble sacrifice.

296
00:16:06,670 --> 00:16:10,870
My gosh.
Am I not like a tragic princess?

297
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:14,810
You know... Who was it?
The one who betrayed her father...

298
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:17,380
- and chose love instead.
- Princess Nakrang?

299
00:16:17,650 --> 00:16:19,880
My, so she was a princess?

300
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:22,990
No wonder
I felt such a kinship with her.

301
00:16:23,620 --> 00:16:27,260
Hey, Woo Jae! Call Dr. Han already!

302
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:29,790
Why don't you believe
the words of a princess?

303
00:16:49,450 --> 00:16:51,950
It seems Woo Jae
really doesn't believe me.

304
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,280
In that case...

305
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:56,850
I'll just have to take matters
into my own hands.

306
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:01,090
Sorry, who did you say
this was again?

307
00:17:02,860 --> 00:17:04,330
Woo Jae's girlfriend?

308
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:07,630
Woo Jae doesn't have a girlfriend.

309
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:09,600
Who is this?

310
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:13,100
Oh, Yang Dong Ik's daughter?

311
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:15,170
What's this about?

312
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:19,640
This is a very urgent matter,
so I decided to call you directly.

313
00:17:19,980 --> 00:17:23,650
After all, whatever concerns you
is my business, too.

314
00:17:24,980 --> 00:17:29,390
Dr. Han, about my stepmom,
she really did go to Seoul.

315
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:31,220
What did you just say?

316
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:34,790
I'm saying, she went to Seoul
to find an apartment for my brother.

317
00:17:36,990 --> 00:17:40,300
You little brat!
What do you think you're doing?

318
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:43,570
What?
I'm just doing the right thing!

319
00:17:49,970 --> 00:17:51,580
This is driving me crazy.

320
00:17:55,250 --> 00:17:57,450
And she had the nerve to play dumb?

321
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:00,920
Wait a minute. The coffee shop.

322
00:18:02,590 --> 00:18:04,390
Why didn't I think of that?

323
00:18:06,660 --> 00:18:09,530
- Honey.
- You're back? And your patients?

324
00:18:10,530 --> 00:18:13,160
Hey, what's going on, everyone?

325
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:17,300
Here, let's all watch this.
I got it from the coffee shop.

326
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:28,650
What is this?

327
00:18:30,010 --> 00:18:31,010
What's this?

328
00:18:36,390 --> 00:18:39,620
- What?
- My goodness. Who is that?

329
00:18:39,820 --> 00:18:40,860
Unbelievable.

330
00:18:41,260 --> 00:18:42,260
- What the...
- No way.

331
00:18:44,330 --> 00:18:45,330
What?

332
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:48,370
- Unbelievable!
- Oh, my word.

333
00:18:49,230 --> 00:18:51,200
- That's...
- Good grief!

334
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:53,470
Who is that?

335
00:18:53,570 --> 00:18:56,440
Mom, what do you mean, who?
It's Bucket's wife.

336
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:59,710
So after all this,
that woman just played dumb?

337
00:19:00,010 --> 00:19:02,780
See? I told you there was no way
I was mistaken.

338
00:19:02,780 --> 00:19:06,980
My goodness. How could she?
She's got some nerve, hasn't she?

339
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:09,550
- That jerk! I ought to...
- Hey!

340
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:11,590
- Jeong Han.
- Dad!

341
00:19:11,590 --> 00:19:14,590
- Jeong Han.
- Mom! We can't let this go, can we?

342
00:19:14,730 --> 00:19:16,560
I am absolutely not
letting this slide!

343
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:19,460
Of course.
We can sue her for this, Mom.

344
00:19:19,460 --> 00:19:20,630
- This is a lawsuit.
- Yes!

345
00:19:22,070 --> 00:19:23,400
What should I do, Mother?

346
00:19:23,970 --> 00:19:25,540
I'll do whatever you say, Mother.

347
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:34,880
Welcome.

348
00:19:45,060 --> 00:19:47,820
I figured you wouldn't want coffee
this late,

349
00:19:48,090 --> 00:19:49,630
so I ordered tea instead.

350
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:52,900
I assume you know
why I asked you to meet.

351
00:19:54,030 --> 00:19:55,030
Yes.

352
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,700
When I found out that
Eun Bin had spoken to you,

353
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:02,340
I called the coffee shop
to try and smooth things over,

354
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:07,680
but they said you'd already checked
the CCTV footage.

355
00:20:08,650 --> 00:20:13,180
- I was taking the CCTV to the cops.
- Dr. Han, please.

356
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:16,850
I may be sitting here right now,

357
00:20:17,220 --> 00:20:20,620
but in your mind,
please picture me on my knees.

358
00:20:21,630 --> 00:20:22,630
Excuse me?

359
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:26,830
If I were to actually kneel here,
everyone would stare,

360
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:29,530
and that would put you
in an awkward position, Dr. Han.

361
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:32,770
What game are you playing?

362
00:20:32,870 --> 00:20:36,870
I am truly, sincerely sorry,
Dr. Han.

363
00:20:36,940 --> 00:20:38,040
Sorry for what?

364
00:20:38,810 --> 00:20:40,310
For taking that photo
and posting it,

365
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:43,350
for deleting it
to destroy the evidence,

366
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:46,380
for tarnishing your reputation,

367
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:49,750
and for nearly
destroying your career.

368
00:20:50,190 --> 00:20:51,420
At least you know what you did.

369
00:20:53,090 --> 00:20:54,420
I just really...

370
00:20:55,530 --> 00:20:59,730
wanted my husband to become
Merchants' Association President.

371
00:21:00,100 --> 00:21:04,530
He could use it as a stepping stone
to run for city council.

372
00:21:06,540 --> 00:21:08,310
As you know,

373
00:21:08,610 --> 00:21:11,740
I'm my husband's second wife.

374
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:14,010
All the love his first wife
couldn't give him,

375
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:17,650
I want to be the one
to give it all to him.

376
00:21:18,950 --> 00:21:22,850
I suppose if you can justify
your wrongful actions with a motive,

377
00:21:23,820 --> 00:21:25,820
you think it'll feel less shameful.
Is that it?

378
00:21:27,790 --> 00:21:28,790
Pardon?

379
00:21:28,860 --> 00:21:32,930
People who disregard moral standards
to satisfy their own desires...

380
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:38,100
rarely feel guilty,
and their apologies aren't sincere.

381
00:21:40,170 --> 00:21:41,770
My goodness.

382
00:21:42,140 --> 00:21:45,040
Are you saying
my apology wasn't sincere?

383
00:21:45,410 --> 00:21:48,650
No, that's not it.
I'm completely sincere, Dr. Han.

384
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:51,350
You're skilled at manipulating
people's feelings,

385
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:55,590
and you're more angry you got caught
than sorry for what you did.

386
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:58,290
That's not true.

387
00:21:59,220 --> 00:22:02,760
I'm really not that complicated.

388
00:22:04,430 --> 00:22:08,730
First of all, I've taken down
all the photos and the post.

389
00:22:08,930 --> 00:22:10,770
And if you want to sue me
for damages,

390
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:13,970
I'm prepared to offer you
a generous settlement.

391
00:22:14,470 --> 00:22:15,710
Well...

392
00:22:15,910 --> 00:22:19,010
Is there anything else...

393
00:22:19,580 --> 00:22:21,340
you might want?

394
00:22:21,910 --> 00:22:23,050
Like...

395
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:24,920
withdrawing from the race?

396
00:22:25,780 --> 00:22:27,420
Is that what you're hoping for?

397
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:32,060
Don't withdraw from the race.

398
00:22:32,690 --> 00:22:35,960
Winning by default
just isn't my style.

399
00:22:37,430 --> 00:22:38,430
Oh, my.

400
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:41,330
Thank you so much, Dr. Han.

401
00:22:44,670 --> 00:22:47,070
So, I guess that means...

402
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:49,870
we've settled things today, right?

403
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:53,840
Thank you.

404
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:06,260
You forgave her, Seong Mi?

405
00:23:06,490 --> 00:23:09,930
I know, right?
You should've torn her hair out.

406
00:23:10,190 --> 00:23:11,900
Seriously,
are you just going to let it slide?

407
00:23:12,430 --> 00:23:15,530
Then what? Sue her and start a war?
We live in the same neighborhood.

408
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:17,400
You did the right thing.

409
00:23:18,070 --> 00:23:19,500
Yes. You did the right thing.

410
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:22,570
- You're staying for dinner, right?
- Yes.

411
00:23:24,410 --> 00:23:27,980
Let's put this behind us
and win fair and square.

412
00:23:28,380 --> 00:23:32,020
Wait, they're not playing fair,
so why should we?

413
00:23:32,350 --> 00:23:33,480
I said to forget it, didn't I?

414
00:23:34,520 --> 00:23:35,850
Woo Jae, spare me a minute.

415
00:23:37,190 --> 00:23:38,190
Okay.

416
00:23:40,420 --> 00:23:43,160
I'm heading out.
I'm going to go study for a bit.

417
00:23:43,230 --> 00:23:46,330
Honey, I'll come pick you up
at the bus stop later. Okay?

418
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:51,070
- Hey.
- Yes.

419
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:56,110
Jeong Han.

420
00:23:57,140 --> 00:23:58,680
Are you really going to play fair?

421
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:00,740
No.

422
00:24:01,850 --> 00:24:02,850
I knew it.

423
00:24:03,310 --> 00:24:04,550
You're not going to let this slide,
are you?

424
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:08,220
- Of course not.
- Right.

425
00:24:10,150 --> 00:24:12,620
- How dare they...
- The nerve.

426
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:18,360
Are you...

427
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:21,930
- dating Yang Dong Ik's daughter?
- What?

428
00:24:22,430 --> 00:24:23,900
No, Mom.

429
00:24:24,130 --> 00:24:27,170
This isn't the "You should study,
not date" lecture.

430
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:28,410
You're old enough.

431
00:24:29,110 --> 00:24:31,110
You can date whoever you want.

432
00:24:31,740 --> 00:24:32,810
Just not her.

433
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:36,180
Did Eun Bin tell you?
That her stepmom was behind this?

434
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:38,720
And how messed up is that?

435
00:24:39,250 --> 00:24:41,080
Stay away from them, son. I mean it.

436
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:43,550
That woman, Eun Bin's stepmother...

437
00:24:43,950 --> 00:24:46,090
Psychoanalytically speaking,

438
00:24:46,090 --> 00:24:48,160
her emotional responses
are abnormal.

439
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:50,830
To put it simply,
she's a crazy witch.

440
00:24:51,660 --> 00:24:53,660
- Mom.
- Don't you forget it.

441
00:24:53,760 --> 00:24:56,270
Seong Mi, I need a word with you.

442
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,640
Yes, Mother! Remember what I said.

443
00:25:00,070 --> 00:25:01,140
Yang Eun Bin, you!

444
00:25:01,670 --> 00:25:03,640
Do you have any idea
what you've done?

445
00:25:04,940 --> 00:25:06,640
And you just had to
go tattle to Dad?

446
00:25:06,980 --> 00:25:11,150
Hey, how could you?
I know you hate her, but come on.

447
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:12,580
Aren't you one of us?

448
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:16,620
Why wouldn't I be?
She's the outsider, not me.

449
00:25:16,690 --> 00:25:19,190
- What was that, you little brat?
- What? Am I wrong?

450
00:25:19,420 --> 00:25:20,420
Yang Eun Bin!

451
00:25:21,390 --> 00:25:24,900
Didn't I tell you I'd kick you out
if you disrespected your stepmother?

452
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,960
Dad, please, just go inside.

453
00:25:27,230 --> 00:25:29,530
I'll give her a stern talking-to,
okay?

454
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:33,340
Please go inside
and get some rest, Father.

455
00:25:33,670 --> 00:25:35,410
We're just talking.

456
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:40,680
Raise your voice one more time,
and I won't let it slide.

457
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:47,250
Happy now? Are you satisfied that
the whole family is yelling at me?

458
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:49,150
Unbelievable.

459
00:25:58,300 --> 00:26:00,130
Hui Gyeong? Birth control pills?

460
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:04,500
My gosh, I just don't understand.
Why would she do that?

461
00:26:04,940 --> 00:26:07,300
Apparently, she doesn't want
to have a baby.

462
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:11,740
What? Dae Han's wanted a baby
for five years.

463
00:26:13,140 --> 00:26:14,710
That's what I'm saying.

464
00:26:15,950 --> 00:26:18,010
I was just so flabbergasted.

465
00:26:18,650 --> 00:26:21,080
You think it's about money?

466
00:26:22,520 --> 00:26:24,960
She said no.
I already asked her that.

467
00:26:25,360 --> 00:26:26,820
There's no way that's true.

468
00:26:27,660 --> 00:26:30,690
She was asking me about
every detail of my contract,

469
00:26:31,030 --> 00:26:32,730
and she keeps holding it over me
that they had to move in...

470
00:26:32,730 --> 00:26:34,430
because they gave me
their security deposit.

471
00:26:36,930 --> 00:26:37,970
You think so?

472
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:41,300
Maybe she's just saying no, thinking
it'll make me uncomfortable?

473
00:26:42,040 --> 00:26:43,240
That's possible.

474
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:46,340
Oh, boy.

475
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:56,420
Mom, I'll drive you
and take the bus back.

476
00:26:56,750 --> 00:27:00,720
Why not come to my studio tomorrow
and bring my things back here?

477
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:03,430
Your things? What for?

478
00:27:04,330 --> 00:27:06,200
I'm moving back here.

479
00:27:06,700 --> 00:27:11,370
- I put my studio on the market.
- What? Really?

480
00:27:11,530 --> 00:27:13,200
Seong Mi.

481
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:15,510
Seong Mi, are you sure about this?

482
00:27:16,070 --> 00:27:19,110
The commute might be tough,
but I'll manage.

483
00:27:19,710 --> 00:27:22,310
Hey, shouldn't you have talked to me
about this first?

484
00:27:22,750 --> 00:27:25,050
And when have you ever talked to me
about anything?

485
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:28,080
I'll make sure to get
every last thing.

486
00:27:28,890 --> 00:27:30,520
Hey, are you sure you'll be okay?

487
00:27:30,850 --> 00:27:32,720
My room will be too cramped. Right?

488
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:34,720
And you need space
to write your book.

489
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:40,930
Dae Han, once the studio is leased,
I'll give you the security deposit,

490
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:42,270
so you can start looking
for a place of your own.

491
00:27:42,570 --> 00:27:43,770
For you and your wife to move into.

492
00:27:45,170 --> 00:27:48,410
- Our own place?
- Yes. You're newlyweds, after all.

493
00:27:48,670 --> 00:27:51,270
It's been weighing on me
that you moved in because of me.

494
00:27:52,280 --> 00:27:55,780
Once your room is free,
I'll use it as my office.

495
00:27:56,610 --> 00:27:58,920
Seong Mi,
is this really because of us?

496
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:00,450
It's for a number of reasons.

497
00:28:00,820 --> 00:28:03,750
I'm tired of people thinking
we're separated or something,

498
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:06,520
and I think I need
to get along better with Ju Ah.

499
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:09,060
I'm so sorry, Seong Mi.

500
00:28:10,060 --> 00:28:11,430
But I bet my wife will be thrilled.

501
00:28:14,260 --> 00:28:15,400
I don't know how to face you.

502
00:28:17,930 --> 00:28:18,970
Thank you,

503
00:28:20,300 --> 00:28:21,810
and you made the right choice.

504
00:28:23,110 --> 00:28:25,540
In a way, I'm kind of grateful
to that family.

505
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:29,010
I think we made the right call
deciding to let it go, Dad.

506
00:28:29,380 --> 00:28:32,780
Grateful? I'm still furious
with them. You know?

507
00:28:59,210 --> 00:29:00,240
All right, let's go.

508
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:10,090
(The 16th Onjeong Market Merchants'
Association Presidential Election)

509
00:29:19,430 --> 00:29:21,970
(The expert who knows
Onjeong Market best)

510
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:30,740
(The go-to doctor
for Onjeong Market merchants)

511
00:29:30,910 --> 00:29:33,980
Bucket.

512
00:29:38,410 --> 00:29:39,550
Oh, shoot.

513
00:29:40,380 --> 00:29:44,590
- Hey, what are you doing?
- What? Too childish for you?

514
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:49,060
The more childish the revenge,
the more it gets under their skin.

515
00:29:49,130 --> 00:29:53,030
- Look at this. Look.
- I see it. But why that one?

516
00:29:55,100 --> 00:29:56,500
Come on.

517
00:29:57,230 --> 00:29:58,770
(Gong Jeong Han:
A leader with empathy)

518
00:29:58,840 --> 00:30:00,870
Hey, what are you doing?

519
00:30:01,170 --> 00:30:02,970
You're supposed to draw
on Bucket's face.

520
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:07,180
Hey, if we draw on Bucket's face,
they'll know it was us.

521
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:09,410
- Right.
- Bingo!

522
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:11,850
A reverse-psychology
negative campaign by self-sacrifice?

523
00:30:12,050 --> 00:30:13,180
You're a genius.

524
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:16,250
- I have my moments. Hey.
- Yes.

525
00:30:16,250 --> 00:30:18,890
My face. You got that, right?

526
00:30:37,670 --> 00:30:38,680
Perfect.

527
00:31:00,430 --> 00:31:02,430
(Number 2 Gong Jeong Han,
Number 1 Yang Dong Ik)

528
00:31:02,430 --> 00:31:03,430
(Rude)

529
00:31:03,530 --> 00:31:05,670
(Toupee! He's bald!)

530
00:31:05,740 --> 00:31:08,140
(Onjeong Market)

531
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:09,470
(Unnecessary treatments,
phony, bald hypocrite)

532
00:31:09,540 --> 00:31:13,210
This is so unbelievably childish.
Don't you think they went too far?

533
00:31:13,280 --> 00:31:16,510
I know, right? How could anyone take
a handsome face like mine...

534
00:31:16,580 --> 00:31:18,750
and ruin it like this?

535
00:31:19,050 --> 00:31:23,250
- Isn't this illegal?
- Yes, it is.

536
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:27,090
Vandalizing a Merchants' Association
poster is destruction of property,

537
00:31:27,220 --> 00:31:28,830
punishable
by up to three years in jail...

538
00:31:28,830 --> 00:31:30,160
or a fine of up to 7,000 dollars.

539
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:32,160
There's CCTV right here, too.
What do you say?

540
00:31:32,900 --> 00:31:35,160
- Should I start an investigation?
- No.

541
00:31:35,670 --> 00:31:38,230
That won't be necessary.
Right, Jeong Han?

542
00:31:38,470 --> 00:31:40,570
That's right. You must be busy.

543
00:31:42,140 --> 00:31:45,510
- All right. I'll be on my way.
- Take care.

544
00:31:47,410 --> 00:31:49,850
(Number 1 Yang Dong Ik)

545
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:54,780
(The Devil of Onjeong Market)

546
00:32:03,790 --> 00:32:04,790
Excuse me...

547
00:32:06,600 --> 00:32:09,400
I can't just stand by
and say nothing.

548
00:32:09,670 --> 00:32:12,900
- Yes?
- He forgave you,

549
00:32:12,900 --> 00:32:14,240
but you aren't even sorry.

550
00:32:14,300 --> 00:32:16,010
How could you let things get worse?

551
00:32:19,980 --> 00:32:21,210
What is she talking about?

552
00:32:21,610 --> 00:32:24,380
To do that to someone's face...

553
00:32:24,450 --> 00:32:27,180
- That's just wrong.
- What is this?

554
00:32:31,720 --> 00:32:36,230
This prank has gone too far, sir.

555
00:32:37,290 --> 00:32:39,060
You should give your children
a talking-to.

556
00:32:43,330 --> 00:32:46,770
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

557
00:32:49,010 --> 00:32:50,810
What have you done?

558
00:32:51,340 --> 00:32:52,440
It wasn't us. What?

559
00:32:52,710 --> 00:32:56,250
- We didn't do it, Dad.
- You pathetic fools.

560
00:32:59,120 --> 00:33:02,090
Tell her I am very sorry.

561
00:33:02,750 --> 00:33:03,990
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

562
00:33:05,890 --> 00:33:08,260
- Dad.
- No, wait.

563
00:33:09,090 --> 00:33:12,160
Hey, when someone lets you off easy,
you should know when to quit.

564
00:33:12,230 --> 00:33:14,500
Have you guys ever heard
of playing fair?

565
00:33:15,230 --> 00:33:16,230
Hey.

566
00:33:16,870 --> 00:33:17,900
Did you do this?

567
00:33:18,270 --> 00:33:20,940
No! You know
I'm not a morning person.

568
00:33:21,740 --> 00:33:23,810
- You did it, didn't you?
- No, I didn't.

569
00:33:24,110 --> 00:33:26,240
Then who could've done it? Who?

570
00:33:26,340 --> 00:33:29,110
You don't really think I'd do this
to my own face, do you?

571
00:33:29,180 --> 00:33:33,280
Exactly.
What kind of lunatic would do that?

572
00:33:34,080 --> 00:33:36,020
Look at that poor guy's face.

573
00:33:36,850 --> 00:33:40,720
- All this for an election? Crazy.
- Seriously.

574
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:41,720
Let's go.

575
00:33:42,430 --> 00:33:43,430
Did you hear that?

576
00:33:48,830 --> 00:33:52,870
It wasn't me!
I swear I didn't do it!

577
00:33:57,670 --> 00:33:59,140
Yes.

578
00:34:02,280 --> 00:34:03,350
Good morning...

579
00:34:51,830 --> 00:34:52,930
What? What the...

580
00:35:01,470 --> 00:35:04,270
- Oh, you're... You're here.
- Yes.

581
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:06,410
Good morning.

582
00:35:06,980 --> 00:35:08,950
I can't believe
it's so late already.

583
00:35:09,580 --> 00:35:11,350
What? Did you sleep here?

584
00:35:11,850 --> 00:35:15,380
My commute is so long,
it just felt like a waste of time.

585
00:35:15,380 --> 00:35:18,960
Gosh, aren't you working too hard?

586
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:20,420
I should get a bed put in here.

587
00:35:23,090 --> 00:35:24,090
Your eyes.

588
00:35:26,430 --> 00:35:27,930
They're totally bloodshot.

589
00:35:29,670 --> 00:35:31,200
No. I'm fine.

590
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:34,740
I got a whole two hours of sleep.

591
00:35:35,810 --> 00:35:37,170
I figured as much,
so I brought you something.

592
00:35:42,610 --> 00:35:46,550
The line here is always long, right?
Did you go right when they opened?

593
00:35:46,620 --> 00:35:49,490
You know my hobby is
hunting down good food.

594
00:35:49,790 --> 00:35:51,890
I gave the design team some, too.
Have some.

595
00:35:53,290 --> 00:35:56,960
Thank you so much.
You're seriously the sweetest.

596
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:03,500
Thank you!

597
00:36:04,300 --> 00:36:06,300
- How about this?
- This is nice.

598
00:36:11,510 --> 00:36:14,210
Wow, it's visually stunning.

599
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:18,010
I went with some bold colors,
focusing on an oversized silhouette.

600
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:20,520
That's very on-trend.

601
00:36:22,490 --> 00:36:24,520
Director Yang,
you should come take a look.

602
00:36:25,420 --> 00:36:27,890
What do I know?
I'm no design expert.

603
00:36:28,390 --> 00:36:31,130
But we need a customer's viewpoint.
Please share your opinion, Director.

604
00:36:38,500 --> 00:36:39,570
Let's see.

605
00:36:41,200 --> 00:36:42,740
How do I put this...

606
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:46,080
(Work order)

607
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:47,840
If this were a meal,

608
00:36:49,710 --> 00:36:52,450
it'd be like a full-course dinner
for breakfast.

609
00:36:54,450 --> 00:36:56,620
I guess
I did get a little too ambitious.

610
00:36:56,950 --> 00:36:59,660
It does seem a little over the top.

611
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:05,430
- Is this your top pick, Mr. Park?
- Yes.

612
00:37:06,160 --> 00:37:08,900
The shirring is meant
to give it a feminine touch.

613
00:37:09,230 --> 00:37:12,500
- It's for functionality.
- Right, but it's a little...

614
00:37:14,900 --> 00:37:16,070
How should I say this...

615
00:37:17,570 --> 00:37:18,840
Like a vitamin supplement?

616
00:37:19,540 --> 00:37:20,540
Excuse me?

617
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:22,110
A vitamin?

618
00:37:22,180 --> 00:37:25,580
You know it's good for you,
but you're never excited to take it.

619
00:37:29,750 --> 00:37:33,120
Should I stop?
My opinion doesn't matter anyway.

620
00:37:33,190 --> 00:37:34,790
Please take a look at mine too,
Director Yang.

621
00:37:35,890 --> 00:37:36,890
All right.

622
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:43,200
Casual sweaters.

623
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:45,740
The yarn adds a special touch,
so it allows for great mobility,

624
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:47,640
and it's stylish, too.

625
00:37:49,010 --> 00:37:50,710
It looks very practical.

626
00:37:52,610 --> 00:37:53,610
But...

627
00:37:56,280 --> 00:37:58,050
it's missing that "wow" factor.

628
00:37:58,650 --> 00:38:01,350
- Excuse me?
- Well, it's like...

629
00:38:02,690 --> 00:38:04,820
If I had to make another analogy,

630
00:38:06,190 --> 00:38:08,890
it's like a well-made rolled omelet.

631
00:38:09,790 --> 00:38:10,930
A rolled omelet?

632
00:38:11,060 --> 00:38:13,500
It's familiar and easy enough
for anyone to make,

633
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:15,800
so it feels more like
an everyday side dish.

634
00:38:17,600 --> 00:38:19,070
A side dish?

635
00:38:19,300 --> 00:38:22,310
To serve this as the main course...

636
00:38:22,410 --> 00:38:25,140
Don't you think
it's lacking that visual hook?

637
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:26,440
What does everyone else think?

638
00:38:35,020 --> 00:38:36,290
You're giving me a death glare,
aren't you?

639
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:39,420
- No, I'm not.
- Yes, you are.

640
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:42,760
That "It's not even your field.
What do you know?" kind of look.

641
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:50,630
Savage.

642
00:38:57,210 --> 00:38:58,310
You're misunderstanding me.

643
00:38:59,340 --> 00:39:00,340
Sure.

644
00:39:01,110 --> 00:39:02,510
Bring on the next one.
This is getting fun.

645
00:39:03,610 --> 00:39:04,710
Ms. Kim So Hye.

646
00:39:11,320 --> 00:39:16,030
All right. I've uploaded everything
and shared the voting link.

647
00:39:17,130 --> 00:39:18,830
Was my design really that bad?

648
00:39:20,430 --> 00:39:25,400
Not bad, just... A bit ordinary.

649
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:28,400
I was so embarrassed
I wanted to die.

650
00:39:28,770 --> 00:39:32,540
What about me? A vitamin? Seriously?
That's not even food!

651
00:39:32,540 --> 00:39:35,540
An omelet?
He and his precious "visual hook."

652
00:39:35,610 --> 00:39:37,680
An omelet? Seriously? Unbelievable.

653
00:39:38,380 --> 00:39:41,450
I'm never eating an omelet again.
I can't even look at one now.

654
00:39:42,120 --> 00:39:45,220
Gosh, just wait for the results of
the Home Shopping investigation.

655
00:39:45,290 --> 00:39:47,320
Then I'm transferring
straight to the design team.

656
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:51,230
What are you talking about?
They're investigating that incident?

657
00:39:51,960 --> 00:39:52,960
The higher-ups are.

658
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:57,670
Why do you look so flustered?

659
00:39:58,530 --> 00:39:59,540
Are you hiding something?

660
00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:02,370
No!
Why would I hide anything from you?

661
00:40:02,740 --> 00:40:04,570
No, that's not it.
It's just... I mean...

662
00:40:04,570 --> 00:40:07,540
I just never thought someone
would've done it on purpose.

663
00:40:08,410 --> 00:40:10,310
Maybe it wasn't on purpose.

664
00:40:10,850 --> 00:40:12,380
Still, we have to find out,
don't we?

665
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:14,980
And if someone did do it on purpose?

666
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:16,720
What are you going to do then?

667
00:40:17,150 --> 00:40:18,420
What do you think I'll do?

668
00:40:18,920 --> 00:40:21,060
I'll kill them.

669
00:40:26,230 --> 00:40:27,230
Woo Jae. Hey, what's up?

670
00:40:28,060 --> 00:40:29,300
Yes. I'm coming home tonight.

671
00:40:29,900 --> 00:40:31,170
Really? In that case...

672
00:40:31,530 --> 00:40:34,000
On your way home, can you stop by
Mom's studio and grab a book for me?

673
00:40:34,270 --> 00:40:36,870
- In the built-in closet.
- She says it's in the closet.

674
00:40:37,210 --> 00:40:39,040
I moved all her stuff out,
but I must have forgotten that.

675
00:40:40,180 --> 00:40:42,280
What are you talking about?
Why would Mom move her things out?

676
00:40:42,650 --> 00:40:45,950
Well...
She decided to move back home.

677
00:40:54,020 --> 00:40:57,190
She was so against living with us,
so why give up her place?

678
00:40:57,790 --> 00:41:01,500
See? She had an affair.
She got caught and is crawling back.

679
00:41:18,010 --> 00:41:19,110
What the...

680
00:41:19,650 --> 00:41:21,320
So she really was having an affair?

681
00:41:28,120 --> 00:41:29,160
Unbelievable.

682
00:41:30,890 --> 00:41:33,330
The nerve of this shameless jerk.

683
00:41:51,380 --> 00:41:52,750
You jerk!

684
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:58,020
You think that hurts?
This hurts me more, you jerk!

685
00:41:59,690 --> 00:42:01,660
Hey! How dare you...

686
00:42:08,500 --> 00:42:10,230
Ms. Gong Ju Ah?

687
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:12,070
Director Yang?

688
00:42:12,540 --> 00:42:15,570
- Wait, what are you doing here?
- What are you doing here...

689
00:42:16,270 --> 00:42:17,270
My gosh!

690
00:42:18,070 --> 00:42:19,070
Oh, man.

691
00:42:19,710 --> 00:42:22,340
How did you even get in here?

692
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:24,450
I used the passcode, of course. I...

693
00:42:25,810 --> 00:42:27,850
More importantly,
what are you doing here?

694
00:42:28,020 --> 00:42:29,220
I just moved in.

695
00:42:29,290 --> 00:42:33,090
- What? This is my mom's apartment.
- What?

696
00:42:33,390 --> 00:42:35,990
Wait, so you're the one who...

697
00:42:36,530 --> 00:42:41,360
So you're the new tenant. Right.

698
00:42:41,430 --> 00:42:44,000
Yes. I guess that's the situation.

699
00:42:45,300 --> 00:42:49,910
Oh, no.
Director Yang, I'm really sorry.

700
00:42:50,440 --> 00:42:51,840
Hey, it's fine.
Things like this happen.

701
00:42:51,910 --> 00:42:54,740
No, it's not that. Your forehead...

702
00:43:00,750 --> 00:43:01,850
Oh, no.

703
00:43:07,960 --> 00:43:10,330
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

704
00:43:14,930 --> 00:43:16,700
I know it was a misunderstanding,
but still...

705
00:43:17,270 --> 00:43:19,030
Do you have to just start wailing
on someone like that?

706
00:43:19,640 --> 00:43:22,910
You should have changed
the passcode then.

707
00:43:23,570 --> 00:43:26,710
And to top it off,
you just had to be showering.

708
00:43:27,040 --> 00:43:30,480
I was a mess from moving everything.

709
00:43:39,220 --> 00:43:43,530
But Director Yang, are you okay?
Take an anti-inflammatory.

710
00:43:45,960 --> 00:43:50,400
Hey, be honest with me.
You recognized me, didn't you?

711
00:43:50,470 --> 00:43:54,200
You did that on purpose, right?
Because I saw your design...

712
00:43:54,670 --> 00:43:56,140
and said it looked like
a rolled omelet.

713
00:43:57,570 --> 00:43:58,740
Of course not!

714
00:43:59,110 --> 00:44:01,680
I'm telling you, I thought
you were my mom's boyfriend.

715
00:44:02,140 --> 00:44:03,150
My gosh.

716
00:44:04,180 --> 00:44:05,280
Your mom's boyfriend?

717
00:44:06,520 --> 00:44:07,820
Oh, it's...

718
00:44:08,180 --> 00:44:11,150
Gosh, it's a personal matter.
Please just forget I said anything.

719
00:44:11,820 --> 00:44:13,020
Right.

720
00:44:16,460 --> 00:44:20,800
So if your mom has an affair,
you get mad at her for it.

721
00:44:21,930 --> 00:44:23,970
Couldn't it be your father's fault,
though?

722
00:44:26,670 --> 00:44:29,410
Well... In any case,

723
00:44:29,410 --> 00:44:32,040
there's no excuse for cheating.

724
00:44:34,610 --> 00:44:35,610
I see.

725
00:44:37,750 --> 00:44:40,780
My mom also had an affair and left.

726
00:44:42,080 --> 00:44:43,150
So why was I...

727
00:44:43,790 --> 00:44:45,590
always so resentful of my father?

728
00:44:51,590 --> 00:44:55,100
Maybe because it's easier to blame
the person who stayed behind?

729
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:35,840
What's this?

730
00:45:36,110 --> 00:45:38,470
"As of today,
I'm no longer your daughter."

731
00:45:39,010 --> 00:45:40,040
"Eun Bin."

732
00:45:40,840 --> 00:45:42,080
Did Eun Bin run away
from home again?

733
00:45:42,680 --> 00:45:45,680
I called Hyun Bin on a hunch,
and he said she's there.

734
00:45:45,980 --> 00:45:47,280
At the studio apartment
Hyun Bin just moved into?

735
00:45:47,680 --> 00:45:48,720
Yes.

736
00:45:53,790 --> 00:45:57,160
- Hey, Gong Woo Jae!
- You scared me. Have some manners.

737
00:45:57,560 --> 00:45:59,830
You should've explained things
properly.

738
00:46:00,130 --> 00:46:03,570
I went to Mom's apartment
and ran into the new tenant.

739
00:46:03,670 --> 00:46:06,070
- You did?
- "You did?"

740
00:46:07,100 --> 00:46:10,540
And guess what?
The new tenant is my director!

741
00:46:11,370 --> 00:46:14,280
- What a weird coincidence.
- "A weird coincidence?"

742
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:19,380
Hey. I hit my director, okay?
I thought he was Mom's boyfriend!

743
00:46:19,450 --> 00:46:22,820
- I smacked him right on the head!
- You've got to be kidding me.

744
00:46:23,420 --> 00:46:26,420
Since when did Mom get a boyfriend?
Seriously, what's wrong with you?

745
00:46:26,490 --> 00:46:28,920
What do you mean?
Mom's having an affair right now.

746
00:46:28,990 --> 00:46:30,460
Those photos caused a huge scandal.

747
00:46:31,490 --> 00:46:34,630
That was the herbal clinic lady's
smear campaign to win the election.

748
00:46:35,560 --> 00:46:37,230
- What?
- The woman from that clinic...

749
00:46:37,230 --> 00:46:39,700
is the one
who took and posted Mom's photo.

750
00:46:39,800 --> 00:46:44,340
- Seriously?
- She was caught and apologized.

751
00:46:45,840 --> 00:46:47,610
That woman is completely insane.

752
00:46:48,740 --> 00:46:49,780
Unbelievable.

753
00:46:53,080 --> 00:46:54,980
Our stepmom is out of her mind,
isn't she?

754
00:46:55,250 --> 00:46:57,750
How could she take a photo like that
in secret...

755
00:46:57,750 --> 00:46:59,560
and try to frame Dr. Han
for an affair?

756
00:47:00,060 --> 00:47:01,690
So that's what happened.

757
00:47:03,060 --> 00:47:05,730
- Stepmom was clearly in the wrong.
- Right?

758
00:47:06,430 --> 00:47:07,560
Seriously.

759
00:47:10,730 --> 00:47:12,500
Wait,
what happened to your forehead?

760
00:47:12,970 --> 00:47:13,970
This?

761
00:47:16,140 --> 00:47:19,140
I guess I took the fall
for what our stepmom did.

762
00:47:20,280 --> 00:47:21,280
What are you talking about?

763
00:47:21,610 --> 00:47:23,210
Is something wrong with your brain?

764
00:47:23,580 --> 00:47:24,580
Gosh, you're so annoying.

765
00:47:27,220 --> 00:47:28,350
This is for the deposit.

766
00:47:29,180 --> 00:47:32,520
Use this to find a place
and put down a deposit.

767
00:47:33,390 --> 00:47:37,790
I figured Mother would tell you
I'm on birth control.

768
00:47:38,430 --> 00:47:41,560
You two don't keep secrets,
after all.

769
00:47:43,470 --> 00:47:47,740
It's not my place to say,
but you know Dae Han wants a child.

770
00:47:48,640 --> 00:47:52,940
And at your age,
it might be hard to conceive.

771
00:47:53,510 --> 00:47:54,510
I know.

772
00:47:54,980 --> 00:47:59,180
Thank you for being so thoughtful.
We'll start trying once we move.

773
00:48:00,820 --> 00:48:03,390
Okay, let's do that. Thank you.

774
00:48:04,090 --> 00:48:05,290
But one more thing...

775
00:48:06,690 --> 00:48:09,490
Can I get the rest of the money
in cash, too?

776
00:48:10,730 --> 00:48:12,890
That's a lot of cash to handle,
isn't it?

777
00:48:13,560 --> 00:48:14,560
Why cash?

778
00:48:15,600 --> 00:48:16,730
You see,

779
00:48:16,930 --> 00:48:21,240
I love the feel of holding cash.
It's for the landlord anyway,

780
00:48:21,340 --> 00:48:24,370
so I can just feel it in my hands
until then.

781
00:48:25,040 --> 00:48:28,180
Honestly.
That's a strange fixation to have.

782
00:48:33,820 --> 00:48:36,750
Hey, what's this?
Why is this door locked?

783
00:48:38,020 --> 00:48:41,190
What? Why don't you just
leave your things there...

784
00:48:41,260 --> 00:48:42,520
until Dae Han's family moves out?

785
00:48:42,790 --> 00:48:45,990
Did you just lock the junk in here
because you were too lazy to clean?

786
00:48:46,230 --> 00:48:48,800
No, that's not it.
I put something important in there.

787
00:48:48,830 --> 00:48:49,830
Just leave it alone.

788
00:48:50,630 --> 00:48:52,000
It's your father's stuff, isn't it?

789
00:48:52,500 --> 00:48:54,670
After you made such a scene
telling your mom to throw it out.

790
00:48:54,970 --> 00:48:57,470
Hey, don't tell Mom. Okay?

791
00:49:00,980 --> 00:49:04,980
The commercial area...

792
00:49:08,650 --> 00:49:11,020
My goodness, this is so long-winded.

793
00:49:11,920 --> 00:49:14,260
Put the last sentence at the start.

794
00:49:14,260 --> 00:49:16,530
Hit them with the main point first.
Be straightforward.

795
00:49:16,760 --> 00:49:18,990
Conclusion first, then explain.
It's easier for people to follow.

796
00:49:19,190 --> 00:49:22,600
Oh, man. Why are you helping me?
I appreciate it.

797
00:49:22,700 --> 00:49:25,070
I'm trying to be a supportive wife.

798
00:49:25,330 --> 00:49:27,870
Just as much as Bucket's wife is.

799
00:49:28,700 --> 00:49:30,970
Look at you holding a grudge.
Goodness.

800
00:49:31,970 --> 00:49:36,080
I'll make sure you're elected
Merchants' Association President.

801
00:49:36,410 --> 00:49:39,610
Because that would be
the best revenge against her.

802
00:49:40,450 --> 00:49:41,650
Gosh, that's scary.

803
00:49:42,020 --> 00:49:44,490
Whatever you do,
don't make that face on TV.

804
00:49:45,520 --> 00:49:46,520
Oh, right.

805
00:49:47,160 --> 00:49:48,990
You should do a TV segment with me.

806
00:49:49,490 --> 00:49:52,830
Director Song wants to air a segment
of us getting along well.

807
00:49:53,160 --> 00:49:56,430
No, forget it.
I'm not cut out for TV.

808
00:49:56,630 --> 00:49:58,000
But they're paying a lot.

809
00:49:58,670 --> 00:50:01,000
Don't tempt me.

810
00:50:01,440 --> 00:50:05,640
How about a premium secondhand
ECG machine?

811
00:50:06,170 --> 00:50:09,750
Due to the burden of rent
and rising labor costs...

812
00:50:09,910 --> 00:50:12,580
- Premium! I said premium.
- The commercial district...

813
00:50:12,650 --> 00:50:13,650
Honey. Premium.

814
00:50:13,880 --> 00:50:17,020
Fine, okay! Deal!
You said premium, right?

815
00:50:18,520 --> 00:50:20,760
I've really been wanting
a premium ECG machine.

816
00:50:21,560 --> 00:50:23,830
- That's right.
- Okay, I'm in.

817
00:50:24,260 --> 00:50:26,360
All right. A premium ECG machine.

818
00:50:29,500 --> 00:50:32,100
- I'm off.
- Okay.

819
00:50:32,500 --> 00:50:34,670
Here.
I know you like these, Seong Mi.

820
00:50:35,170 --> 00:50:39,270
Amazing. I always skipped breakfast.
This is like paradise.

821
00:50:40,380 --> 00:50:44,180
Listen, from now on, you and Ju Ah
should take turns driving.

822
00:50:44,680 --> 00:50:47,380
- Did Ju Ah come home last night?
- Yes.

823
00:50:49,950 --> 00:50:52,190
- I'm off.
- Gong Ju Ah.

824
00:50:52,750 --> 00:50:55,090
- Yes?
- Take your mom's car.

825
00:50:56,320 --> 00:50:58,430
- No, I don't want to.
- Hey!

826
00:51:16,710 --> 00:51:17,710
Sorry about the misunderstanding.

827
00:51:17,980 --> 00:51:19,410
I thought you were having an affair.

828
00:51:19,980 --> 00:51:23,050
A misunderstanding? It wasn't one.
I am having an affair.

829
00:51:23,390 --> 00:51:26,960
I preach adultery, not love.
So what?

830
00:51:27,020 --> 00:51:30,830
Come on, I'm apologizing.
Don't be petty. Forgive me already.

831
00:51:30,960 --> 00:51:33,800
- I have something important today.
- I don't feel like it.

832
00:51:34,100 --> 00:51:36,970
Whether I forgive you or not
is my call.

833
00:51:36,970 --> 00:51:38,100
Unbelievable.

834
00:51:38,400 --> 00:51:41,540
- You accepted Ms. Cha's apology.
- I did. So what?

835
00:51:41,600 --> 00:51:43,770
Why would you forgive her?
After she humiliated you like that.

836
00:51:43,840 --> 00:51:47,880
Suing her would've taught a lesson.
Seriously.

837
00:51:48,780 --> 00:51:51,810
If I did that,
wouldn't I be stooping to her level?

838
00:51:53,150 --> 00:51:56,050
Your mother is a better person
than that woman.

839
00:51:56,820 --> 00:51:58,920
Gosh, what a hypocrite.

840
00:51:59,350 --> 00:52:02,720
Forgiveness isn't hypocrisy.
It's a way to free yourself.

841
00:52:03,090 --> 00:52:06,930
It's not for them,
but to move on from your own anger.

842
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:08,760
It's a decision you make
for self-preservation.

843
00:52:09,430 --> 00:52:10,730
In psychology,

844
00:52:11,330 --> 00:52:14,040
they call it
"forgiveness as maturity."

845
00:52:14,840 --> 00:52:17,140
It means forgiving is a sign
of being mature.

846
00:52:17,670 --> 00:52:19,880
Gosh, I'm sick of this.

847
00:52:20,210 --> 00:52:24,150
By the way, I hear
Bucket's son is back in Korea.

848
00:52:25,210 --> 00:52:27,420
Really? You mean Yang Hyun Bin?

849
00:52:27,680 --> 00:52:31,420
Yes. That woman was looking
for a studio apartment for him.

850
00:52:31,820 --> 00:52:34,120
His office must be somewhere
near my clinic.

851
00:52:35,290 --> 00:52:38,530
Then that must be close
to my office, too.

852
00:53:01,720 --> 00:53:02,720
What?

853
00:53:03,720 --> 00:53:04,720
It's up.

854
00:53:06,350 --> 00:53:07,360
All right, everyone.

855
00:53:07,960 --> 00:53:10,390
Our submission
for the design competition...

856
00:53:11,090 --> 00:53:13,630
Drumroll, please...

857
00:53:14,830 --> 00:53:17,630
It will be revealed in 60 seconds...

858
00:53:23,940 --> 00:53:24,940
Okay.

859
00:53:26,110 --> 00:53:27,110
All right.

860
00:53:28,840 --> 00:53:30,850
Our final submission
for the competition...

861
00:53:32,880 --> 00:53:35,480
is Ms. Kim So Hye's design.

862
00:53:36,220 --> 00:53:37,220
Really?

863
00:53:37,820 --> 00:53:39,990
- Wait, me?
- Yes.

864
00:53:40,290 --> 00:53:42,260
In second place,
by a very narrow margin,

865
00:53:43,390 --> 00:53:44,390
is Ms. Gong Ju Ah.

866
00:53:45,260 --> 00:53:46,260
Oh, man.

867
00:53:47,830 --> 00:53:49,400
Congratulations, So Hye.

868
00:53:50,400 --> 00:53:52,570
Thank you all so much.

869
00:53:53,370 --> 00:53:54,370
Hey, now.

870
00:53:55,100 --> 00:53:57,070
Laugh or cry. Pick one.

871
00:53:57,840 --> 00:54:01,110
Wow, your name will be on the label
for next season's line.

872
00:54:01,710 --> 00:54:04,410
My dad is going to be so happy.

873
00:54:04,750 --> 00:54:07,820
I've always wanted him to wear
something with my name on it.

874
00:54:08,650 --> 00:54:10,750
Gosh, I'm so jealous.

875
00:54:11,550 --> 00:54:15,420
Should we have So Hye take the lead
on the competition project?

876
00:54:15,620 --> 00:54:18,630
Well, I'll handle the colorways,

877
00:54:18,730 --> 00:54:21,930
and it'd be great if you all could
divide up the flats for each item.

878
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:25,130
You're doing the sweater and pants?
Should I take the outerwear then?

879
00:54:25,200 --> 00:54:27,670
Yes. Ms. Gong?

880
00:54:28,100 --> 00:54:30,040
If you wouldn't mind,
could you run the DTP test...

881
00:54:30,040 --> 00:54:31,110
on the outerwear fabric...

882
00:54:31,170 --> 00:54:33,240
and also source the trims
and materials?

883
00:54:33,980 --> 00:54:34,980
Of course.

884
00:55:03,940 --> 00:55:04,940
Are you okay?

885
00:55:06,710 --> 00:55:08,080
No, I'm not.

886
00:55:09,680 --> 00:55:11,350
I'm not going to lie.

887
00:55:18,690 --> 00:55:19,690
Yes.

888
00:55:24,660 --> 00:55:25,990
I understand, Vice President.

889
00:55:29,600 --> 00:55:32,130
Looks like they found the culprit
in the Home Shopping incident.

890
00:55:33,230 --> 00:55:34,240
Let's go.

891
00:55:38,040 --> 00:55:39,770
Tell Mr. Park Jun Hyeok
to come, too.

892
00:55:49,750 --> 00:55:52,650
You think someone really did this
on purpose?

893
00:55:53,220 --> 00:55:54,820
I'm afraid so.

894
00:55:56,290 --> 00:55:57,290
Who?

895
00:55:58,130 --> 00:55:59,130
It can't be.

896
00:56:00,960 --> 00:56:01,960
They're saying it was Kim So Hye.

897
00:56:04,500 --> 00:56:07,870
A staff member said they saw her
swap out the clothes that morning.

898
00:56:08,070 --> 00:56:11,670
If we start disciplinary action,
I'm not sure how they will respond.

899
00:56:12,070 --> 00:56:13,510
If word of this gets out,

900
00:56:14,010 --> 00:56:16,010
it'll be a huge blow
to our brand's image.

901
00:56:16,610 --> 00:56:20,220
You can't ask me to forgive her,
can you?

902
00:56:21,250 --> 00:56:23,690
Ma'am, I'll accept
the disciplinary action.

903
00:56:24,720 --> 00:56:25,720
What? Why you?

904
00:56:26,050 --> 00:56:27,990
Because I'm also responsible
for mismanaging my team member.

905
00:56:28,820 --> 00:56:31,360
- Isn't that why you called me in?
- No.

906
00:56:32,260 --> 00:56:34,260
I'm leaving the decision on
Kim So Hye's disciplinary action...

907
00:56:35,200 --> 00:56:36,830
to the two of you team leaders.

908
00:56:38,830 --> 00:56:40,340
It's not my place to decide.

909
00:56:41,600 --> 00:56:43,470
I'll go with whatever Ju Ah decides.

910
00:56:52,110 --> 00:56:53,110
Why did you do it?

911
00:56:53,750 --> 00:56:56,520
Have you held a grudge against me
all this time?

912
00:56:56,950 --> 00:56:58,020
I'm sorry.

913
00:56:59,550 --> 00:57:01,290
I was just so desperate...

914
00:57:01,560 --> 00:57:03,390
Did you really think
you'd get away with this?

915
00:57:04,360 --> 00:57:05,360
Yes.

916
00:57:06,630 --> 00:57:07,630
What?

917
00:57:07,730 --> 00:57:12,030
I've never thought of you
as being desperate, Ms. Gong.

918
00:57:13,470 --> 00:57:16,370
That's why I honestly had no idea
you were looking into it like this.

919
00:57:17,170 --> 00:57:18,470
I thought
if something like that happened,

920
00:57:19,710 --> 00:57:21,510
you'd just quit.

921
00:57:22,580 --> 00:57:23,650
Why?

922
00:57:23,650 --> 00:57:27,150
You didn't major in design,
and you have a medical license.

923
00:57:27,820 --> 00:57:30,320
You could quit, and you'd be fine,

924
00:57:31,750 --> 00:57:33,390
but this is all I have.

925
00:57:34,660 --> 00:57:37,660
I am so sick and tired
of hearing that.

926
00:57:38,690 --> 00:57:41,330
You don't know how hard I've worked
so I wouldn't have to hear that.

927
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:43,800
You people are unbelievable.

928
00:57:45,670 --> 00:57:47,840
So Hye, for me,

929
00:57:48,070 --> 00:57:50,910
becoming a designer wasn't a choice.

930
00:57:50,910 --> 00:57:52,810
I wanted to be a designer
so badly...

931
00:57:53,110 --> 00:57:54,880
that I gave up everything else
for it.

932
00:57:56,480 --> 00:57:59,050
- I'm sorry.
- And "sorry" makes it okay?

933
00:58:03,520 --> 00:58:04,520
Unbelievable.

934
00:59:03,810 --> 00:59:04,910
Ms. Kim So Hye.

935
00:59:05,580 --> 00:59:06,580
Yes?

936
00:59:14,090 --> 00:59:15,860
What was it
you asked me to do earlier?

937
00:59:16,260 --> 00:59:18,630
The DTP test on the outerwear,
and what was the other thing?

938
00:59:19,630 --> 00:59:21,700
- What?
- Ju Ah.

939
00:59:21,960 --> 00:59:23,770
I can't remember
what else you asked for.

940
00:59:25,230 --> 00:59:27,670
Sourcing the trim and materials...

941
00:59:29,770 --> 00:59:30,840
Ms. Gong...

942
00:59:33,740 --> 00:59:35,610
What are you waiting for?
Are you going to work or not?

943
00:59:36,240 --> 00:59:39,110
Yes. I'll get right on it.
I'll work my hardest.

944
00:59:48,660 --> 00:59:50,860
(Taehan)

945
00:59:51,030 --> 00:59:53,030
(Managing Director
Pacundo Ignacio de la Cruz Yang)

946
00:59:58,900 --> 01:00:00,900
(Taehan Group)

947
01:00:06,470 --> 01:00:09,780
So you're leaving me here alone
to go back to the design office?

948
01:00:10,550 --> 01:00:12,550
You don't need me anymore, Director.

949
01:00:15,480 --> 01:00:19,020
So what should I do with this place?
A meeting room or design space?

950
01:00:19,850 --> 01:00:21,460
Whatever you think is best, sir.

951
01:00:22,960 --> 01:00:26,060
- I'm going to get going...
- Why...

952
01:00:26,530 --> 01:00:29,030
did you let Kim So Hye off the hook?
You should've just fired her.

953
01:00:30,430 --> 01:00:33,170
Then,
as the competition's runner-up,

954
01:00:33,700 --> 01:00:35,570
the collection would've been
released under your name.

955
01:00:37,770 --> 01:00:39,840
Because Kim So Hye's design
was good.

956
01:00:41,010 --> 01:00:44,250
My design might not have even placed
in the competition.

957
01:00:44,710 --> 01:00:46,080
It looked like a rolled omelet.

958
01:00:50,550 --> 01:00:52,750
I made the decision
for the sake of the team.

959
01:00:57,830 --> 01:00:59,260
Even so, if it were me,

960
01:00:59,960 --> 01:01:01,500
I don't think
I could've forgiven her.

961
01:01:04,530 --> 01:01:08,000
My mom was wronged very badly once.

962
01:01:09,000 --> 01:01:13,980
She forgave the one who defamed her
and accused her of an affair.

963
01:01:15,110 --> 01:01:17,350
I couldn't understand
how she could forgive them.

964
01:01:18,410 --> 01:01:21,250
But then, my mom told me something.

965
01:01:22,120 --> 01:01:25,220
"Forgiveness is about
freeing yourself."

966
01:01:25,950 --> 01:01:29,620
"It's not for the other person,
but to escape your own anger."

967
01:01:29,820 --> 01:01:31,690
"It's a way of protecting yourself."

968
01:01:34,900 --> 01:01:36,200
She sounds like an amazing person.

969
01:01:38,000 --> 01:01:40,570
I know. And even though
I can't stand her,

970
01:01:40,640 --> 01:01:43,340
I want to be just like her,
which is ironic.

971
01:01:49,940 --> 01:01:52,880
- I should get going.
- Okay.

972
01:01:53,510 --> 01:01:55,520
(Taehan Group)

973
01:01:59,450 --> 01:02:01,220
- Thank you.
- Sure.

974
01:02:14,270 --> 01:02:15,840
Way to fall for her again,
Yang Hyun Bin.

975
01:02:18,470 --> 01:02:19,810
I shouldn't be feeling this way.

976
01:02:24,680 --> 01:02:27,750
- Here you go, Mom.
- That's enough.

977
01:02:30,180 --> 01:02:33,520
All right, everyone.
The election is finally upon us.

978
01:02:36,760 --> 01:02:40,090
You've worked harder than anyone,
pounding the pavement on a budget.

979
01:02:40,360 --> 01:02:41,930
Come on, it's not over yet.

980
01:02:41,930 --> 01:02:44,300
Let's make a final push
this weekend.

981
01:02:44,430 --> 01:02:45,830
- Let's do it!
- Let's do it!

982
01:02:45,900 --> 01:02:48,100
- Let's have a toast.
- A toast!

983
01:02:48,170 --> 01:02:50,940
- Great idea.
- I'll lead the toast.

984
01:02:51,410 --> 01:02:54,910
To Gong Jeong Han's victory!

985
01:02:54,910 --> 01:02:56,410
- To victory!
- To victory!

986
01:02:56,410 --> 01:02:59,410
Wait. You can do better than that!

987
01:02:59,550 --> 01:03:03,020
Come on!
To Gong Jeong Han's victory!

988
01:03:03,080 --> 01:03:05,990
- To victory!
- To victory!

989
01:03:06,050 --> 01:03:07,990
- Bottoms up!
- Bottoms up!

990
01:03:12,360 --> 01:03:15,100
- Take small sips, okay?
- Dad, this is so good!

991
01:03:17,770 --> 01:03:22,100
Dispatch, this is Mackerel.
Do you copy? Over.

992
01:03:23,910 --> 01:03:27,380
We read you loud and clear.
This is Cutlassfish, over.

993
01:03:28,280 --> 01:03:29,310
Roger that.

994
01:03:30,180 --> 01:03:32,280
(Information, How may I help you?)

995
01:03:32,350 --> 01:03:34,320
(We are here to help
with anything you need.)

996
01:03:35,480 --> 01:03:37,450
Sector A,
campaign routes are overlapping.

997
01:03:37,920 --> 01:03:39,690
Sector B,
expecting heavy crowd congestion.

998
01:03:42,290 --> 01:03:45,660
I'm deploying to the final rally
to prepare for any contingencies.

999
01:03:45,760 --> 01:03:47,400
Stay sharp out there.

1000
01:03:50,770 --> 01:03:53,300
(Kim Chun Hyeon)

1001
01:04:00,880 --> 01:04:02,410
(The go-to doctor
for Onjeong Market merchants)

1002
01:04:02,480 --> 01:04:04,610
(Number 2 Gong Jeong Han)

1003
01:04:04,680 --> 01:04:06,810
(Number 1 Yang Dong Ik)

1004
01:04:06,880 --> 01:04:08,880
(Number 2 Gong Jeong Han)

1005
01:04:08,950 --> 01:04:10,920
(Number 1 Yang Dong Ik)

1006
01:04:10,990 --> 01:04:12,890
(Number 2 Gong Jeong Han)

1007
01:04:12,950 --> 01:04:14,890
(Number 1 Yang Dong Ik)

1008
01:04:39,850 --> 01:04:42,820
Hyun Bin,
can I please just live with you?

1009
01:04:43,020 --> 01:04:45,590
I don't want to live
with my stepmom.

1010
01:04:45,650 --> 01:04:48,020
She's doing the best she can.

1011
01:04:48,490 --> 01:04:50,930
Even when she makes bad decisions,

1012
01:04:51,330 --> 01:04:54,530
I try to understand
that she's doing it for our family.

1013
01:04:55,600 --> 01:04:56,830
I don't understand her.

1014
01:04:58,630 --> 01:05:01,640
Eun Bin.
But you like her, don't you?

1015
01:05:01,970 --> 01:05:05,810
You're scared of getting hurt
because you like her so much.

1016
01:05:05,870 --> 01:05:07,680
So you're pushing her away
on purpose, right?

1017
01:05:08,240 --> 01:05:10,440
No, you're wrong!
What do you know, anyway?

1018
01:05:15,320 --> 01:05:16,380
I hate you!

1019
01:05:26,290 --> 01:05:27,300
There.

1020
01:05:28,030 --> 01:05:29,560
All done with the workshop prep.

1021
01:05:31,230 --> 01:05:32,930
I'm starving. What should I get?

1022
01:05:34,170 --> 01:05:35,170
Pork cutlet?

1023
01:05:36,240 --> 01:05:38,970
That pork cutlet place I went to
with Yang Hyun Bin...

1024
01:05:39,040 --> 01:05:40,370
I should go there.
It's been a while.

1025
01:05:43,940 --> 01:05:45,610
But wait.

1026
01:05:46,250 --> 01:05:48,980
Yang Hyun Bin...
He's back but hasn't even called.

1027
01:05:49,950 --> 01:05:53,020
And his office is nearby, I think.
I wonder which apartment he's in.

1028
01:05:53,990 --> 01:05:54,990
Hold on.

1029
01:05:55,720 --> 01:06:00,700
Come to think of it,
He and the director are so alike.

1030
01:06:01,960 --> 01:06:04,870
Okay, let's see. First of all,
they both have the surname, Yang.

1031
01:06:05,200 --> 01:06:08,340
They both studied abroad,
their families are similar,

1032
01:06:09,000 --> 01:06:11,510
they live in an apartment
near my office,

1033
01:06:12,440 --> 01:06:14,540
and their parents' house
is also near here...

1034
01:06:15,340 --> 01:06:16,840
Pork cutlet is my absolute favorite.

1035
01:06:18,150 --> 01:06:21,380
Right,
and they both love pork cutlet.

1036
01:06:21,680 --> 01:06:24,150
- What else...
- You look strangely familiar.

1037
01:06:25,420 --> 01:06:27,250
He said I looked familiar, too.

1038
01:06:28,190 --> 01:06:29,320
No way...

1039
01:06:29,620 --> 01:06:31,460
Director, what's your Korean name?

1040
01:06:35,700 --> 01:06:36,830
Yang Hyun Bin.

1041
01:06:40,940 --> 01:06:44,640
(Love Pork Cutlet)

1042
01:06:48,010 --> 01:06:49,710
This place hasn't changed a bit.

1043
01:06:55,450 --> 01:06:57,390
- One pork cutlet, please.
- Okay.

1044
01:07:10,230 --> 01:07:11,770
I've decided to study abroad.

1045
01:07:13,930 --> 01:07:15,170
I promise I'll come back.

1046
01:07:16,600 --> 01:07:18,040
Don't you ever forget me.

1047
01:07:18,810 --> 01:07:21,440
Yes. I'll remember.

1048
01:07:35,090 --> 01:07:36,160
Liar.

1049
01:07:37,390 --> 01:07:39,130
As if you were going to remember
anyway.

1050
01:07:45,770 --> 01:07:47,900
- Can I get some water, please?
- Yes.

1051
01:08:31,810 --> 01:08:34,520
(Recipe For Love)

1052
01:08:34,580 --> 01:08:37,220
- I studied abroad and never called.
- Why?

1053
01:08:37,280 --> 01:08:39,150
Because we were never meant to be.

1054
01:08:39,150 --> 01:08:40,920
What? Are your families feuding?

1055
01:08:40,920 --> 01:08:42,160
- Yes.
- What?

1056
01:08:43,160 --> 01:08:44,590
- One more time.
- One more time.

1057
01:08:44,660 --> 01:08:48,160
- We prescribe...
- Love!

1058
01:08:48,230 --> 01:08:50,900
Hello, everyone.

1059
01:08:50,970 --> 01:08:54,540
- Bucket's son had a crush on you.
- You knew?

1060
01:08:54,670 --> 01:08:57,710
Marriage is never something
you get to decide for yourself.

1061
01:08:58,510 --> 01:09:01,780
- We'll begin the election vote...
- Move.

1062
01:09:01,840 --> 01:09:04,250
for the 16th President of
the Onjeong Merchants' Association.
